      "statement": "r(justifies <-> selects_endpoints) > r(justifies <-> cites_as_support) in the schizophrenia evidence chain. Justification (d1) and endpoint selection (d2) are mechanistically coupled: the positive-symptom theory of dopamine excess directly constrains which endpoints are selected (PANSS positive subscale, BPRS). Citation (d3=cites_as_support) encodes a more diffuse, institutionally amplified coupling because guidelines and regulatory approvals create circular citation loops back to the founding hypothesis. In a partially circular chain (stronger mechanistic grounding than M_MED1/M_MED3 but still institutionally self-referential), the d1-d2 coupling should exceed d1-d3 coupling, replicating the gradient direction found in M_MED1 h1 (PARTIAL) and M_MED3 h1 (PARTIAL). If DENIED: this would indicate that the schizophrenia chain is MORE institutionally locked-in than antidepressants or opioids, with citation patterns aligning more tightly to the theoretical structure than endpoint selection does -- a stronger form of circularity. Note: n=10 limits statistical power; direction is the primary criterion."
